A colonoscopy is the gold standard for detecting colorectal cancer. A colonoscopy/sigmoidoscopy is a diagnostic procedure where a small camera is used to look inside your rectum and intestine to check for cancer and to even remove precancerous growths. It only needs to be repeated every 10 years. However, the procedure is not free, requires sedation, and is more invasive, and thus it cannot be done here--we can only help you arrange an appointment.

**For patients with significant risk factors for CRC (i.e. primary family history, bloody stools), we strongly recommend for you to schedule a colonoscopy.**
